{"query": {"pages": {"509331": {"lastrevid": 634014523, "pageid": 509331, "canonicalurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pappus%27s_centroid_theorem", "title": "Pappus's centroid theorem", "editurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Pappus%27s_centroid_theorem&action=edit", "length": 2358, "contentmodel": "wikitext", "pagelanguage": "en", "touched": "2015-02-14T13:05:20Z", "ns": 0, "fullurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pappus%27s_centroid_theorem", "revisions": [{"*": "<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Pappus_centroid_theorem_areas.gif\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/Pappus_centroid_theorem_areas.gif/400px-Pappus_centroid_theorem_areas.gif\" width=\"400\" height=\"240\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/fd/Pappus_centroid_theorem_areas.gif 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/fd/Pappus_centroid_theorem_areas.gif 2x\" data-file-width=\"500\" data-file-height=\"300\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Pappus_centroid_theorem_areas.gif\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The theorem applied to an open cylinder, cone and a sphere to obtain their surface areas. The centroids are at a distance <i>a</i> (in red) from the axis of rotation.</div></div></div>\n<p>In mathematics, <b>Pappus' centroid theorem</b> (also known as  the <b>Guldinus theorem</b>, <b>Pappus\u2013Guldinus theorem</b> or <b>Pappus' theorem</b>) is either of two related <a href=\"/wiki/Theorem\" title=\"Theorem\">theorems</a> dealing with the <a href=\"/wiki/Surface_area\" title=\"Surface area\">surface areas</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Volume\" title=\"Volume\">volumes</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/Surface_of_revolution\" title=\"Surface of revolution\">surfaces</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Solid_of_revolution\" title=\"Solid of revolution\">solids</a> of revolution.\n</p><p>The theorem is attributed to <a href=\"/wiki/Pappus_of_Alexandria\" title=\"Pappus of Alexandria\">Pappus of Alexandria</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Paul_Guldin\" title=\"Paul Guldin\">Paul Guldin</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div id=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#The_first_theorem\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The first theorem</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#The_second_theorem\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The second theorem</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Generalizations\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Generalizations</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_first_theorem\">The first theorem</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pappus%27s_centroid_theorem&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: The first theorem\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The first theorem states that the <a href=\"/wiki/Surface_area\" title=\"Surface area\">surface area</a> <i>A</i> of a <a href=\"/wiki/Surface_of_revolution\" title=\"Surface of revolution\">surface of revolution</a> generated by rotating a <a href=\"/wiki/Plane_curve\" title=\"Plane curve\">plane curve</a> <i>C</i> about an <a href=\"/wiki/Axis_of_rotation\" title=\"Axis of rotation\" class=\"mw-redirect\">axis</a> external to <i>C</i> and on the same plane is equal to the product of the <a href=\"/wiki/Arc_length\" title=\"Arc length\">arc length</a> <i>s</i> of <i>C</i> and the distance <i>d</i> traveled by its <a href=\"/wiki/Centroid\" title=\"Centroid\">geometric centroid</a>.\n</p>\n<dl><dd> <img class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline tex\" alt=\"A = sd.\\,\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/math/f/2/f/f2f2bfa911e4e8ec126662e1b1caa22d.png\" /></dd></dl>\n<p>For example, the surface area of the <a href=\"/wiki/Torus\" title=\"Torus\">torus</a> with minor <a href=\"/wiki/Radius\" title=\"Radius\">radius</a> <i>r</i> and major radius <i>R</i> is \n</p>\n<dl><dd> <img class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline tex\" alt=\"A = (2\\pi r)(2\\pi R) = 4\\pi^2 R r.\\,\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/math/4/2/2/42287f0e33a3112943d28cf2903dae11.png\" /></dd></dl>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_second_theorem\">The second theorem</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pappus%27s_centroid_theorem&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: The second theorem\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The second theorem states that the <a href=\"/wiki/Volume\" title=\"Volume\">volume</a> <i>V</i> of a <a href=\"/wiki/Solid_of_revolution\" title=\"Solid of revolution\">solid of revolution</a> generated by rotating a <a href=\"/wiki/Plane_figure\" title=\"Plane figure\" class=\"mw-redirect\">plane figure</a> <i>F</i> about an external axis is equal to the product of the area <i>A</i> of <i>F</i> and the distance <i>d</i> traveled by its geometric centroid.\n</p>\n<dl><dd> <img class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline tex\" alt=\"V = Ad.\\,\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/math/9/f/c/9fca105001fe12ddfbd2b372224f3438.png\" /></dd></dl>\n<p>For example, the volume of the <a href=\"/wiki/Torus\" title=\"Torus\">torus</a> with minor radius <i>r</i> and major radius <i>R</i> is \n</p>\n<dl><dd> <img class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline tex\" alt=\"V = (\\pi r^2)(2\\pi R) = 2\\pi^2 R r^2.\\,\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/math/b/1/7/b17570773cdcdac01efba7acb0477828.png\" /></dd></dl>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Generalizations\">Generalizations</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pappus%27s_centroid_theorem&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Generalizations\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The theorem can be generalized for arbitrary curves and shapes, under appropriate conditions.<sup id=\"cite_ref-generalizations_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-generalizations-1\"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pappus%27s_centroid_theorem&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-generalizations-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-generalizations_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><span id=\"generalizations\" class=\"citation web\">Goodman, A. W.; Goodman, G. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.jstor.org/discover/10.2307/2316426?uid=2129&amp;uid=2&amp;uid=70&amp;uid=4&amp;sid=21104382078753\">\"Generalizations of the Theorems of Pappus\"</a>. <i>JSTOR</i>. The American Mathematical Monthly<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2014-06-28</span></span>.</span><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APappus%27s+centroid+theorem&amp;rft.atitle=Generalizations+of+the+Theorems+of+Pappus&amp;rft.aufirst=A.+W.&amp;rft.au=Goodman%2C+A.+W.&amp;rft.au=Goodman%2C+G.&amp;rft.aulast=Goodman&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fdiscover%2F10.2307%2F2316426%3Fuid%3D2129%26uid%3D2%26uid%3D70%26uid%3D4%26sid%3D21104382078753&amp;rft.jtitle=JSTOR&amp;rft.pub=The+American+Mathematical+Monthly&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pappus%27s_centroid_theorem&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><span class=\"citation mathworld\" id=\"Reference-Mathworld-Pappus.27s_Centroid_Theorem\"><a href=\"/wiki/Eric_W._Weisstein\" title=\"Eric W. Weisstein\">Weisstein, Eric W.</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://mathworld.wolfram.com/PappussCentroidTheorem.html\">\"Pappus's Centroid Theorem\"</a>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/MathWorld\" title=\"MathWorld\">MathWorld</a></i>.</span></li></ul>\n"}]}}}, "warnings": {"query": {"*": "Formatting of continuation data will be changing soon. To continue using the current formatting, use the 'rawcontinue' parameter. To begin using the new format, pass an empty string for 'continue' in the initial query."}}}